---
export const prerender = false;
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Research";
---

<BaseLayout title={pageTitle}>
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>From Timeline to Runtime</h1>
    <p class="section-intro">
      My journey from non-linear editing to generative code.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="narrative-content">
    <div class="chapter">
      <span class="chapter-marker">01</span>
      <h2>The Frame</h2>
      <p>
        I started as a <strong>Video Editor</strong>. I was obsessed with the
        timeline—cutting seconds, rearranging moments, finding the rhythm in
        chaos. But the timeline is fixed. Once rendered, it never changes.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter">
      <span class="chapter-marker">02</span>
      <h2>The Keyframe</h2>
      <p>
        I moved to <strong>Motion Design</strong>. Keyframes gave me control
        over time and physics. I could make things bounce, float, and shatter.
        Yet, it was still a loop. A pre-calculated simulation of reality.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="chapter">
      <span class="chapter-marker">03</span>
      <h2>The Runtime</h2>
      <p>
        Now, I build <strong>Interactive Systems</strong>. I want to create
        visuals that push back. Large-scale installations where the audience
        isn't just watching, but influencing the art in real-time. Code is the
        new lens.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="cta-container">
      <a href="/research/lab" class="lab-button">
        <span class="btn-text">Enter The Lab</span>
        <span class="btn-icon">→</span>
      </a>
      <p class="cta-sub">
        Access the archive of visual experiments and prototypes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .page-header {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
      padding-top: var(--space-lg);
      text-align: center;
    }

    .page-header h1 {
      font-size: 3rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .section-intro {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-family: "Space Mono", monospace;
    }

    .narrative-content {
      max-width: 680px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 4rem;
    }

    .chapter {
      position: relative;
      padding-left: 2rem;
      border-left: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    }

    .chapter-marker {
      position: absolute;
      left: -2.5rem;
      top: 0;
      font-family: "Space Mono", monospace;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--text-tertiary);
      opacity: 0.5;
    }

    .chapter h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      color: var(--text-primary);
    }

    .chapter p {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    .chapter strong {
      color: var(--text-primary);
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .cta-container {
      margin-top: 2rem;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 3rem 0;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    }

    .lab-button {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 1rem;
      background: var(--text-primary);
      color: var(--bg-color);
      padding: 1rem 2rem;
      border-radius: 100px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      transition:
        transform 0.2s ease,
        opacity 0.2s ease;
    }

    .lab-button:hover {
      transform: scale(1.02);
      opacity: 0.95;
    }

    .cta-sub {
      margin-top: 1rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--text-tertiary);
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
